<br>
&quot;We've been awaiting your arrival Vasilissa.&quot; Yes, she still knew Yakut as Queen.<br>
<br>
&quot;My pardons Yakut for intruding . . .  my name is Azia. I'm the Queen's personal Shamaness.&quot;<br>
Sure enough, tattooed on her hand she bore the mark of the Shaman.<br>
<br>
&quot;Something has happened Yakut. Weeks ago Raven vanished from the lands. She spoke of darkness emerging and the death of peace.&quot; She looked clueless.<br>
&quot;We knew nothing that she spoke to us, only that she said that the Valley's greatest strength, would now bring forth it's destruction. We sent word to Scynthia to try and locate you, and Alysia said you were on your way.&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked worried and confused. She then pointed down towards the trail of the River.<br>
<br>
&quot;She's been there for days. No one knows why, and none of us dare to question her.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=amazonprincessraven>Amazon Princess Raven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(8/13/02 8:18:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Darkness vanishing</span><hr size=1> Sure enough, Raven sat there in the middle of the river. She was mumbling words as other approached her. She wore short leathers and her headdress sat on the riverbank so as not to get wet and destroyed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Peace has died within bloodshed of innocent.&quot; She spoke almost as if dazing off.<br>
<br>
As they came closer they would see that she was scrubbing her wrists with rocks. &quot;I'll get them off if it kills me.&quot;<br>
<br>
Only Yakut would know what Raven was truly doing. She was trying to rid herself of the marks of Dakor. Tiny red dots that lined her wrists in a pattern of the Dark God. <br>
Her efforts were failing, and all she was doing was bleeding her hands.<br>
<br>
&quot;I can't allow my tribe to fall.&quot;<br>
<br>
The peace that had died was Yakut. Raven knew in her heart what had happened. Yakut lost the innocence and Raven knew then that the Peace that the Valley once stood for would die . . . the only way Raven herself kept the peace was with Yakut's strength . . . and to her, that was now gone. Raven's darkness would soon emerge, and in her mind, it would destroy the tribe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonqueenyakut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen</span><br>  Posts: 169<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(8/14/02 4:01:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Darkness....</span><hr size=1> Yakut went to the river and found her daughter Raven. The Shamaness eyes were stinging with tears, as she took off her headress and walked into the water. The still Former Queen stealthly and slowly got closer. She easily and gently as possible removed the rocks from Raven's hand and let them fall into the water.<br>
<br>
