<br>
&quot;There is no such thing as peace . . . Not while darkness lives in the world.&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked over and saw her step-mother and sisters along with another woman. This must be her Aunt Shy. She never met her, but since the rest of the family was all about the peace, she had a feeling that she wouldn't be liked much by her.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm the outcast. And while nothing is good in the world, I'm the only one who can protect us all.&quot;<br>
<br>
She finally realised this.<br>
<br>
&quot;Mother you need to return for good to us here. The tribe needs you. I'm not good at keeping the peace.&quot;<br>
<br>
All of a sudden, there was a sound comming loudly through the bushes. While Yakut's happy little family stood on the bank of the river, a large boar came charging at the little ones who stood short compared to the others.<br>
<br>
Raven's bright blue eyes flickered black momentarilly as her hand went outward towards the bank of the river. Dark light flew from the small dots on her wrist and just as the boar was about to hit her younger sisters, the light hit the beast tearing him to burnt pieces. Silence fell upon them all as Raven then looked to Yakut.<br>
<br>
&quot;See . . . only darknes resides.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonqueenyakut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen</span><br>  Posts: 170<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(8/15/02 6:39:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/cristalc15/images/yakut.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Eeep.</span><hr size=1> Yakut watched as all played out before her eyes. The Shamaness didn't know what to do.<br>
<br>
&quot;Raven, you are not an outcast. If anything I am the one who is a stranger among her own. How many Amazons bear no weapons? Hm? I mean evertyone is different. Tanna, Me, Glory, Ariel, Lynn, Shyriana....You are a True Amazon, its in your blood. I am your blood.&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked to the shore where Tanna, her two daughters and twin sister Shyriana stood.<br>
<br>
&quot;They are apart of me, and you too. Wether or not you know it.&quot;<br>
<br>
Raven probably still had a &quot;thing&quot; with Christanna but Christanna is Ariel's blood mother and Yakut's wife.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have returned to Tanais River Valley, you, the Tribe to help you rule. I think that it would be good for you to..&quot; <br>
<br>
Yakut can't believe she's about to say this,<br>
<br>
 &quot;raise an Army and Protect the Valley. Be War Queen. I'll keep my peace and handle the domestic affairs. We can give Scynthia a rest from protecting us. They have enough problems of their own.&quot;<br>
<br>
The Shamaness sighed. Darkness would always plague her and her family but that's just life. Might suck but its life.<br>
<br>
&quot;And no matter what you say, Peace lives. Just not in the way you think....I love you and so does everyone on that shore.&quot;<br>
<br>
She looks over at the rest of her family. Family. Her hues return to Raven.<br>
<br>
&quot;Dakor might have taken away alot of things from you but he can never take your family away. Or your Amazon blood.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yakut would never give up on Raven or anyone in her family or the Amazon Nation for that fact. Yakut's dedication was strong and her love was even stronger.<br>
<br>
&quot;You see Raven...your one of us. Your my daughter, my family.&quot; <p>§-:¦:-§ Yakut §-:¦:-§ <BR>
