&quot;Hi,Ravey.&quot; She smiled wide,then looked at Ravens wrists. &quot;Does that hurt,when you do that?&quot; A thin brow quirked. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonqueenyakut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(8/21/02 4:10:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/cristalc15/images/yakut.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How Cute</span><hr size=1> Yakut watched Raven and Glory with a smirk for a few minutes before turning towards her hut. She stopped the wagon cart and began unloading all the family's stuff. <br>
<br>
--------------------<br>
<br>
Night Time came, and by that time Yakut had unpacked all the stuff and stabled her horses. She had placed the wagon cart behind the stables for anyone to use.<br>
<br>
The Shamaness walked to the bon fire and sat down on the ground leaning back on the log.<br>
<br>
&quot;I hate re-unpacking.&quot;<br>
<br>
She had mumbled this to herself while staring into the flames. <p>§-:¦:-§ Yakut §-:¦:-§ <BR>
